@node "Usage" "Usage          "

 @{u}@{fg shine}USAGE@{uu}@{fg text}

 Startup:
 /kusr [flags]

 The optional flags will be shown in the listview at startup,
 default is to list all the entries in your userlist.

 You can also list multiple flags at once each flag group should be separated
 by |.

 E.g. "bot|d" will list all entries matching "bot" (vop) AND "d" (Note this
 is not the same as listing vopd).


 User List page:
 - Click            : show the data from the selected user in the "User"
                      gadgets.
 - List by          : users with matching flags that will be listed in the
                      listview, multiple flags (see above) are allowed.
 - Del User         : remove the current selected user from the user list.

 - Nick, Flags, Host: enter/change the user data here.
 - Update User      : update the selected user with the current data.
 - Add User         : add the defined user to the user list. Note that the
                      user will only be shown in the listview if his flags
                      match the current defined flags in the "List by" gadget.
 - Clear            : clear the User gadgets.

 User Flags page:
 If you're not that good in remembering the user flags, you can use this page
 to set them.

 Clicking on a user in the listview will update the selected flags.

 Changing the "List by" flags will result in updating of the selected flags,
 when multiple flags (not the "bot" or "all" buttons) are used the last flags
 group (the one(s) after the last |) is used to update the User Flags page.

 - Set List Flags   : set the "List by" gadget with the currently set flags
                      (this will also result in relisting of the users with
                      matching flags).
 - Set Nick Flags   : set the "User" flags gadget with the currently set
flags.

 Global options:
 - Save             : save the currently active user list to disk, this will
                      make the changes permanent.
 - Reload           : reload the user from memory, this will undo any changes
                      made to the user list since last "Update User" or /addf
                      in amirc.
 - Reload from Disk : reload the user from disk, this will undo any changes
                      made to the user list since you last saved it.
 - Quit             : Exit Kuang11USR.
@endnode

